=title> My Anime idea (Comments please)</span><hr size=1> Aaaaaannnnnnnyways...<br>
<br>
I've started making my own anime. It started out as an experiment with Windows movie maker (Using bitmaps as still clips and shortening the length to make each 'frame', and then combining it with AVI clips produced using 3D Canvas), but now I'm 3 minutes into the first episode and I'm getting a bit concerned that my plot is a little half-baked (I'm kinda making it up as I go along). So here's a synopsis of the plot and any comments/criticisms and suggestions (especially of a name for the anime) would be appreciated. <br>
<br>
Okay.... Yoshi is a relatively normal 18 year old guy who lives with his Grandfather in Osaka in 2018. His grandfather runs a martial arts dojo and a Japanese restaurant. Yoshi is trained at the dojo (after college) and also works in the restaurant. One day, Reiko Kiyonari a 20 year old female mercenary/assasin (A hired gun, if you can afford it, she'll kill it) and her associate Miku meet in the restaurant for lunch. Reiko and Yoshi do NOT get along as she is rude and aggressive towards him (Although Miku is more friendly). However, the (relative) calm is shattered when a sniper tries (but fails) to shoot Reiko. Reiko chases the sniper to a block of flats, looking for revenge, but the sniper proves to be a tough opponent. Yoshi shows up to help, but the sniper still won't be beaten.<br>
<br>
Then Miku uses Reiko's Harrier (A British made fighter jet capable of vertical take off) to fire a missile into the flats. The sniper dies, but Reiko and Yoshi get out alive. Reiko offers Yoshi a drink, but her goodwill is shortlived when Miku screws up the landing, totally wrecking the jet. Reiko holds Yoshi personally responsible and hands him a bill for $23 million. Yoshi wakes up the next day convinced the whole thing was a dream, but is shocked to find Reiko in his room. Reiko tells him that she and Miku have moved in until Yoshi can pay her back the $23 million, adding that she expects him to assist in her 'work' until he has settled the debt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sevenwingangel>Seven Wing Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/19/03 10:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Anime idea (Comments please)</span><hr size=1> Well so far that sounds like a really interesting introduction, most animes dont' start out with anything deep or clever, but slowly introduce them as the series plays out.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teamorangextreme>Team Orange Xtreme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/20/03 1:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My anime idea</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the positive comments! Do you h